Description: Analyse correlations between observed variables and posterior
    distributions of latent variables (estimated hierarchically or separately
    for each subject). Uses a "plausible values" approach based on posterior
    draws to properly account for uncertainty, enabling inference on the
    correlation coefficient at both the sample and population level without
    re-fitting the latent variable model. Includes tools for calculating,
    summarising, visualising, and comparing plausible correlations.
